1
00:00:13,722 --> 00:00:16,852
(gentle music)

2
00:00:16,934 --> 00:00:18,944
‐ [Ruri] Everything
started on Mars,

3
00:00:19,019 --> 00:00:22,479
and now it looks like everything
may end on Mars as well.

4
00:00:22,564 --> 00:00:25,694
Whatever the case, it looks
like we’ll be fumbling about,

5
00:00:25,817 --> 00:00:28,487
making a lot of noise
until the very end.

6
00:00:28,570 --> 00:00:29,650
However, when you
think about it,

7
00:00:29,738 --> 00:00:32,698
I guess that’s rather
appropriate for us.

8
00:00:33,825 --> 00:00:37,695
("You Get to Burning"
by Yumi Matsuzawa)

9
00:00:52,970 --> 00:00:56,850
(singing in foreign language)

10
00:02:05,542 --> 00:02:08,092
(ominous music)

11
00:02:14,843 --> 00:02:18,143
‐ Hey, what in the
heck is going on here?

12
00:02:18,263 --> 00:02:20,103
Why are these guys
all retreating?

13
00:02:20,182 --> 00:02:21,562
‐ Well, there’s not much point

14
00:02:21,642 --> 00:02:23,102
in fighting at the
moment, is there?

15
00:02:23,185 --> 00:02:25,155
I doubt that you’ll
keep firing on the ruins

16
00:02:25,228 --> 00:02:26,808
with both Akito and Ms.
Fressange down there.

17
00:02:26,938 --> 00:02:29,768
So, I guess we’ll
just have to wait

18
00:02:29,858 --> 00:02:31,988
and see how this works out.

19
00:02:32,069 --> 00:02:32,819
‐ Akito.

20
00:02:35,364 --> 00:02:37,664
‐ Just how deep is
this thing, anyway?

21
00:02:37,741 --> 00:02:40,451
‐ Well, according to
our research, it’s
about 10 kilometers

22
00:02:40,535 --> 00:02:43,745
deep, with distortion fields
in place every 800 meters.

23
00:02:43,830 --> 00:02:46,500
But who does the doctor
plan on greeting?

24
00:02:46,625 --> 00:02:48,335
‐ [Akito] I don’t know.

25
00:02:48,460 --> 00:02:49,210
(gasping)

26
00:02:49,336 --> 00:02:50,166
‐ Could it be Ai?

27
00:02:50,295 --> 00:02:51,125
‐ Huh?

28
00:02:51,213 --> 00:02:51,753
‐ Of course!

29
00:02:51,838 --> 00:02:52,798
‐ Of course!

30
00:02:52,881 --> 00:02:54,421
‐ We of course.

31
00:02:54,508 --> 00:02:56,048
‐ If it’s Ai, that explains why

32
00:02:56,176 --> 00:02:58,136
the doctor was acting
a little strange.

33
00:02:58,220 --> 00:02:59,430
‐ What I don’t understand is how

34
00:02:59,513 --> 00:03:01,513
you can say it’s Ai so easily.

35
00:03:01,640 --> 00:03:03,020
‐ Could the Ais have it?

36
00:03:03,141 --> 00:03:05,061
‐ Now, wait just a darn second!

37
00:03:05,185 --> 00:03:07,055
Would someone care
to explain just who

38
00:03:07,187 --> 00:03:09,017
this Ai is that you’re
all talking about?

39
00:03:09,147 --> 00:03:10,937
‐ Did you say explanation?

40
00:03:11,024 --> 00:03:13,694
Since the explanation lady
has shut off her transmission,

41
00:03:13,777 --> 00:03:16,237
I’ll act as her substitute.

42
00:03:16,363 --> 00:03:19,533
Ai is a young girl Mr. Tenkawa
met in the utopia colony

43
00:03:19,616 --> 00:03:22,156
shortly before he Boson
Jumped from Mars to Earth,

44
00:03:22,244 --> 00:03:24,584
and whose apparent
death caused Mr. Tenkawa

45
00:03:24,705 --> 00:03:26,335
a great deal of
personal anguish.

46
00:03:26,415 --> 00:03:29,545
However, it would appear
that Ai is not dead.

47
00:03:29,668 --> 00:03:31,288
‐ [Ai] Isn’t he here yet?

48
00:03:31,378 --> 00:03:33,458
‐ [Inez] Hold on,
he’ll be here soon.

49
00:03:33,547 --> 00:03:34,917
‐ [Ai] Okay.

50
00:03:35,048 --> 00:03:37,088
‐ Unfortunately, with all
those distortion fields

51
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:39,047
blocking his path I’m
afraid that it’s going to be

52
00:03:39,136 --> 00:03:40,546
difficult for him to get here.

53
00:03:40,679 --> 00:03:42,349
(Ai giggling)

54
00:03:42,431 --> 00:03:43,471
Is something wrong?

55
00:03:43,557 --> 00:03:44,927
‐ You smell nice, old lady.

56
00:03:45,058 --> 00:03:46,728
(laughing)
‐ Do I seem that old to you?

57
00:03:46,852 --> 00:03:48,392
‐ Just like mommy.

58
00:03:48,478 --> 00:03:49,188
‐ Huh?

59
00:03:49,271 --> 00:03:50,521
‐ You smell just like my mommy.

60
00:03:50,605 --> 00:03:53,185
But mommy went to sleep
and wouldn’t wake up

61
00:03:53,275 --> 00:03:55,365
and then there
was this big boom,

62
00:03:55,444 --> 00:03:56,744
and it was dark.

63
00:03:56,862 --> 00:03:59,612
Then Mr. Akito started
shining really bright,

64
00:03:59,740 --> 00:04:01,990
and there was this crazy
sound and I started running.

65
00:04:02,075 --> 00:04:03,865
Wait for me, wait for me!

66
00:04:03,952 --> 00:04:06,082
Mr. Akito, wait for me!

67
00:04:06,204 --> 00:04:07,914
‐ There’s a free falling object

68
00:04:08,039 --> 00:04:09,749
approaching from above, captain.

69
00:04:09,875 --> 00:04:11,585
(wind whistling)

70
00:04:11,668 --> 00:04:13,588
(object crashing)

71
00:04:13,712 --> 00:04:14,712
‐ What the heck was that?

72
00:04:14,796 --> 00:04:16,416
‐ [Man] Analyzing.

73
00:04:16,506 --> 00:04:17,546
(computers beeping)

74
00:04:17,632 --> 00:04:19,512
‐ Mam, object is
a Jovian Chulip.

75
00:04:19,593 --> 00:04:20,723
(gasping)

76
00:04:20,802 --> 00:04:21,592
(object crashing)
(woman screaming)

77
00:04:21,678 --> 00:04:22,758
Damage to our starboard engine.

78
00:04:22,888 --> 00:04:25,098
Field shrink down 20%.

79
00:04:25,182 --> 00:04:27,232
We were hit with
a gravity blast!

80
00:04:27,309 --> 00:04:27,929
‐ What?

81
00:04:28,018 --> 00:04:30,978
(dramatic music)

82
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:32,904
‐ [Man] Completed
analyzing enemy strike.

83
00:04:32,981 --> 00:04:35,691
Two phase transition
core powered battleships,

84
00:04:35,776 --> 00:04:37,026
one of which is the Nadesico!

85
00:04:37,110 --> 00:04:38,440
‐ It’s the Nadesico?

86
00:04:38,528 --> 00:04:39,528
Did you hear that captain?

87
00:04:39,613 --> 00:04:41,533
At last, we’re finally
going to get a rematch.

88
00:04:41,615 --> 00:04:42,705
‐ So it seems.

89
00:04:42,783 --> 00:04:44,123
Well, let’s see
what that dashing

90
00:04:44,201 --> 00:04:46,491
man of action will do this time.

91
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:47,950
(dramatic music)

92
00:04:48,079 --> 00:04:49,659
‐ [Man] The Kannazuki
is advancing, captain.

93
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:51,330
‐ [Tsukiomi] Hail the Kannazuki.

94
00:04:51,458 --> 00:04:52,128
‐ [Man] Yes sir.

95
00:04:52,209 --> 00:04:53,289
‐ Tell them to deploy all robots

96
00:04:53,418 --> 00:04:55,668
for combat deployment
immediately.

97
00:04:55,796 --> 00:04:56,956
(dramatic music)

98
00:04:57,047 --> 00:04:57,797
‐ I’m scared!

99
00:04:57,923 --> 00:05:00,433
‐ It’s going to be fine.

100
00:05:00,509 --> 00:05:01,679
What’s going on?

101
00:05:01,802 --> 00:05:04,432
‐ Ms. Fressange, a Jovian
Chulip just came out of nowhere,

102
00:05:04,513 --> 00:05:06,643
and started launching
battleships and gyros at us.

103
00:05:06,723 --> 00:05:09,393
‐ So, the close proximity
of the Jovian Boson Jump

104
00:05:09,476 --> 00:05:12,436
must be what caused the ruins
to accelerate their activity.

105
00:05:12,521 --> 00:05:13,481
‐ [Ai] Huh?

106
00:05:13,563 --> 00:05:14,313
‐ It really is Ai!

107
00:05:14,397 --> 00:05:17,567
‐ Ms. Fressange, are you there?

108
00:05:17,651 --> 00:05:19,071
Ms. Fressange!

109
00:05:19,152 --> 00:05:21,202
‐ Multiple mobile enemies
weapons approaching.

110
00:05:21,321 --> 00:05:23,871
‐ We’ll have to handle the
ones who are closest first.

111
00:05:23,990 --> 00:05:24,700
Ryoko?

112
00:05:24,825 --> 00:05:25,835
‐ I got you, captain.

113
00:05:25,951 --> 00:05:27,161
Just let me at ’em.

114
00:05:27,244 --> 00:05:28,664
‐ Prepare the gravity
blast cannon, Jun.

115
00:05:28,745 --> 00:05:29,905
‐ [Jun] Yes mam.

116
00:05:29,996 --> 00:05:31,366
‐ I’m detecting
enemy Gekigan type

117
00:05:31,498 --> 00:05:33,708
units approaching
via Boson Jump.

118
00:05:33,834 --> 00:05:36,504
(dramatic music)

119
00:05:37,879 --> 00:05:40,339
(Ai gasping)

120
00:05:41,675 --> 00:05:43,845
‐ [Inez] Akito, please hurry.

121
00:05:43,927 --> 00:05:45,297
(dramatic music)

122
00:05:45,387 --> 00:05:46,637
‐ [Akatsuki] This
is the last barrier.

123
00:05:46,721 --> 00:05:47,851
Keep pushing forward.

124
00:05:47,931 --> 00:05:50,181
‐ Right, I’m coming
as fast as I can Ai!

125
00:05:50,267 --> 00:05:51,017
Hold on!

126
00:05:51,101 --> 00:05:53,561
‐ Hurry, hurry Mr. Akito, hurry!

127
00:05:53,687 --> 00:05:56,607
Oh, I don’t wanna go lady!

128
00:05:56,690 --> 00:05:57,820
I wanna stay!

129
00:05:57,899 --> 00:05:59,689
I wanna see Akito!

130
00:05:59,818 --> 00:06:01,068
‐ You will.

131
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:04,324
Maybe not now, but you
will someday, trust me.

132
00:06:04,406 --> 00:06:06,656
You’re a strong girl,
Ai, I know you are.

133
00:06:06,741 --> 00:06:08,201
That’s why you need to believe,

134
00:06:08,326 --> 00:06:11,116
why you can never forget
his face, his voice.

135
00:06:11,204 --> 00:06:13,544
No matter what happens you
can’t forget those things.

136
00:06:13,665 --> 00:06:16,085
Please don’t forget,
promise me you won’t, Ai.

137
00:06:16,209 --> 00:06:18,499
‐ Uh huh, I won’t, I promise!

138
00:06:18,587 --> 00:06:21,877
I won’t ever, ever
forget Mr. Akito, lady.

139
00:06:21,965 --> 00:06:23,635
(gasping)
Oh, I forgot!

140
00:06:23,717 --> 00:06:26,087
When I got here, I was
supposed to give you this.

141
00:06:26,219 --> 00:06:28,049
They asked me to
give this to you.

142
00:06:28,179 --> 00:06:31,719
(electricity buzzing)
(metal clanking)

143
00:06:31,850 --> 00:06:34,560
(ominous music)

144
00:06:38,815 --> 00:06:40,395
‐ [Inez] The gift.

145
00:06:41,693 --> 00:06:44,243
(men screaming)

146
00:06:46,781 --> 00:06:47,571
‐ Ai!

147
00:06:48,742 --> 00:06:50,742
Ms. Fressange, where’s Ai?

148
00:06:50,869 --> 00:06:52,079
‐ You just missed her.

149
00:06:52,203 --> 00:06:54,373
That’s why I told you to hurry.

150
00:06:54,456 --> 00:06:56,616
But, maybe it was
meant to be like this.

151
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:58,250
‐ What’s that mean?

152
00:06:58,335 --> 00:07:01,465
‐ The first letter
in Inez is I, Akito.

153
00:07:01,588 --> 00:07:02,378
‐ Huh?

154
00:07:02,464 --> 00:07:03,464
(Inez chuckling)

155
00:07:03,590 --> 00:07:05,130
‐ She was thinking of
you when she jumped,

156
00:07:05,258 --> 00:07:06,928
but because you were
Boson Jumping to the earth

157
00:07:07,010 --> 00:07:07,930
she got lost.

158
00:07:08,011 --> 00:07:09,471
‐ [Akito] What?

159
00:07:09,596 --> 00:07:10,846
‐ She ended up on ancient
Mars and the people who built

160
00:07:10,931 --> 00:07:13,431
this ruin sent her back, and
thanks to everything that

161
00:07:13,558 --> 00:07:16,268
just happened, she just
jumped again, and ended up

162
00:07:16,353 --> 00:07:17,733
in the middle of
the Martian desert

163
00:07:17,812 --> 00:07:20,312
where she was found
wandering 20 years ago.

164
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:22,360
You know what
happened after that.

165
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:24,942
You saw it when all of our
memories were joined together,

166
00:07:25,028 --> 00:07:26,568
when you saw my memories.

167
00:07:26,655 --> 00:07:27,825
‐ Are you saying...

168
00:07:29,115 --> 00:07:30,615
‐ [Inez] You saw it
too, right Akatsuki?

169
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:32,120
‐ That’s right.

170
00:07:32,243 --> 00:07:33,793
‐ And of course all of the
other pilots, the captain,

171
00:07:33,912 --> 00:07:35,372
and Ruri saw it as well.

172
00:07:35,455 --> 00:07:37,745
‐ I see, and that incident
must have been when

173
00:07:37,832 --> 00:07:40,962
you started to recover
your memory, am I correct?

174
00:07:41,044 --> 00:07:42,554
‐ That’s right.

175
00:07:42,629 --> 00:07:44,419
The little girl lost all of
her memory from the shock

176
00:07:44,506 --> 00:07:46,046
of being left in the desert.

177
00:07:46,132 --> 00:07:48,472
Fortunately, she was
found and rescued by some

178
00:07:48,593 --> 00:07:50,553
Nergal researchers, and
eventually she was‐‐

179
00:07:50,637 --> 00:07:51,677
‐ Wait, I know that!

180
00:07:51,805 --> 00:07:53,315
I know all of this!

181
00:07:53,390 --> 00:07:55,560
But I just never put all
the pieces together before.

182
00:07:55,642 --> 00:07:58,352
I’m so sorry, Ai, I
should have saved you.

183
00:07:58,478 --> 00:08:01,148
(Inez sniffling)
‐ It’s so wonderful

184
00:08:01,231 --> 00:08:02,731
to see you again, mister.

185
00:08:04,776 --> 00:08:06,316
(wind whistling)

186
00:08:06,444 --> 00:08:08,864
‐ Okay, okay, I
understand, I got it!

187
00:08:08,989 --> 00:08:11,869
It’s a time thing, some kind
of chronological paradox

188
00:08:11,992 --> 00:08:13,492
or whatever you call it, right?

189
00:08:13,618 --> 00:08:16,078
Now, if I could tear you
away from your soap opera,

190
00:08:16,162 --> 00:08:19,172
the Kakitsubata really
needs some cover here!

191
00:08:19,249 --> 00:08:21,169
‐ [Yurika] That’s true,
it’s as if the Kakitsubata

192
00:08:21,292 --> 00:08:23,542
was being attacked
by rabid octopi.

193
00:08:23,670 --> 00:08:26,840
(dramatic music)

194
00:08:26,965 --> 00:08:28,265
(shots firing)

195
00:08:28,341 --> 00:08:30,511
‐ It’s said that he who
hunts two hares loses both.

196
00:08:30,593 --> 00:08:32,433
Therefore, we shall deal
with this other ship

197
00:08:32,512 --> 00:08:33,852
before focusing our attention

198
00:08:33,930 --> 00:08:35,680
on the more formidable Nadesico.

199
00:08:35,807 --> 00:08:36,847
Saburota!

200
00:08:36,933 --> 00:08:38,733
‐ I know what you mean, sir.

201
00:08:38,852 --> 00:08:41,852
Gekigan punch!

202
00:08:41,980 --> 00:08:43,560
‐ Erina, abandon ship!

203
00:08:43,690 --> 00:08:44,270
‐ What, but‐‐

204
00:08:44,357 --> 00:08:45,857
‐ Just do it, damn it!

205
00:08:45,984 --> 00:08:48,694
(dramatic music)

206
00:08:48,778 --> 00:08:51,198
(explosions detonating)

207
00:08:52,866 --> 00:08:55,026
‐ [Saburota] Gekigan beam!

208
00:08:55,160 --> 00:08:57,790
(explosion detonating)

209
00:08:57,871 --> 00:08:58,911
‐ The Kakitsubata!

210
00:08:59,039 --> 00:09:00,539
‐ It exploded!

211
00:09:00,665 --> 00:09:03,875
‐ Erina Won, blown to bits
along with her ambitions.

212
00:09:04,002 --> 00:09:05,212
‐ I was not blown up!

213
00:09:05,295 --> 00:09:07,055
‐ Let’s pray.
(sobbing)

214
00:09:07,172 --> 00:09:08,672
‐ Hey, I said I wasn’t dead!

215
00:09:08,757 --> 00:09:09,337
‐ [Izumi] Yes, you are.

216
00:09:09,424 --> 00:09:11,804
‐ [Erina] No, I’m not!

217
00:09:11,885 --> 00:09:12,935
‐ [Akito] It’s all my fault.

218
00:09:13,053 --> 00:09:13,893
‐ You’re wrong!

219
00:09:14,012 --> 00:09:15,562
You mustn’t blame yourself!

220
00:09:15,638 --> 00:09:18,098
‐ The Ai that I met two
years ago was a sweet

221
00:09:18,224 --> 00:09:19,774
and innocent little girl.

222
00:09:19,893 --> 00:09:22,853
But when I jumped she was
somehow sent back in time

223
00:09:22,937 --> 00:09:24,017
and lost her memory.

224
00:09:24,105 --> 00:09:25,645
She grew up to be a dried out,

225
00:09:25,732 --> 00:09:27,942
walking encyclopedia
because of me.

226
00:09:28,068 --> 00:09:29,108
‐ [Girl] But you didn’t know,

227
00:09:29,235 --> 00:09:31,065
and you can’t
change anything now.

228
00:09:31,154 --> 00:09:32,614
‐ [Woman] That’s right.

229
00:09:32,739 --> 00:09:33,949
‐ [Woman] Come on, Mr. Akito,
have an nice a rice bowl.

230
00:09:34,074 --> 00:09:35,074
(women chattering)

231
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:37,370
‐ [Akito] No, I’m not‐‐
(women chattering)

232
00:09:37,452 --> 00:09:38,622
‐ [Girl] Eat it, eat it!

233
00:09:38,745 --> 00:09:39,705
(Akito mumbling)
(women chattering)

234
00:09:39,788 --> 00:09:42,158
(bell chiming)

235
00:09:42,248 --> 00:09:44,328
‐ I’ve got to go
now, big brother.

236
00:09:44,417 --> 00:09:46,337
There are too many things
that need doing right now

237
00:09:46,419 --> 00:09:47,879
and I’ve got to help.

238
00:09:47,962 --> 00:09:50,262
But I swear, I’ll make
your dream come true.

239
00:09:50,340 --> 00:09:53,720
(wind whistling)

240
00:09:53,802 --> 00:09:55,512
‐ [Tsukiomi] What’s the
status of the enemy ship?

241
00:09:55,595 --> 00:09:56,845
‐ [Man] No movement detected.

242
00:09:56,930 --> 00:09:58,390
They’ve gone completely silent

243
00:09:58,473 --> 00:10:00,393
since they descended
into the ruin excavation.

244
00:10:00,475 --> 00:10:01,855
‐ Hail the enemy vessel.

245
00:10:01,935 --> 00:10:03,025
‐ [Man] Yes sir.

246
00:10:03,103 --> 00:10:04,103
‐ Tell them to abandon the ruin

247
00:10:04,229 --> 00:10:05,859
and surrender their
ship to us immediately.

248
00:10:05,939 --> 00:10:08,899
‐ If you surrender within
30 minutes you have my word

249
00:10:08,983 --> 00:10:11,493
as the commander of this battle
group that I will guarantee

250
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:14,991
the safety of your crew,
sincerely, The Jovians.

251
00:10:15,115 --> 00:10:16,665
‐ [Group] Hmm.

252
00:10:16,783 --> 00:10:18,743
‐ It certainly looks like
we’re completely cornered.

253
00:10:18,827 --> 00:10:19,947
So, what now, Captain?

254
00:10:20,078 --> 00:10:21,538
‐ Well, we can’t surrender,

255
00:10:21,621 --> 00:10:24,421
