509
00:19:06,604 --> 00:19:07,314
‐ [Akito] Go away where?

510
00:19:07,396 --> 00:19:08,606
‐ [Yurika] (Mumbles).

511
00:19:08,689 --> 00:19:09,399
‐ [Akito] Ow, you
hit me, my eye!

512
00:19:09,482 --> 00:19:11,482
(both chattering)

513
00:19:11,567 --> 00:19:12,647
‐ [Yurika] Get out of my way!

514
00:19:12,735 --> 00:19:14,155
‐ And what was that?

515
00:19:14,278 --> 00:19:16,738
‐ It sounds like a couple
arguing on an open comm channel.

516
00:19:16,822 --> 00:19:17,612
‐ Huh?

517
00:19:17,698 --> 00:19:18,488
‐ [Akito] Let go!

518
00:19:18,616 --> 00:19:20,076
‐ [Yurika] You let go!

519
00:19:20,159 --> 00:19:21,329
‐ [Akito] Come on, please?
‐ [Yurika] I don’t want to!

520
00:19:21,410 --> 00:19:22,490
‐ Jeez will you please
start using your brain

521
00:19:22,620 --> 00:19:24,000
and stop being so stubborn?

522
00:19:24,080 --> 00:19:24,830
‐ Me?

523
00:19:24,914 --> 00:19:26,124
And when will you realize I was

524
00:19:26,207 --> 00:19:27,997
just trying to help you and Ai?

525
00:19:28,084 --> 00:19:29,924
‐ What are you talking
about, you nut bar?

526
00:19:30,002 --> 00:19:31,882
‐ I know how guilty you
feel about what happened

527
00:19:32,004 --> 00:19:33,634
to Ms. Fressange,
which is the reason

528
00:19:33,714 --> 00:19:36,224
why I tried to turn back time.

529
00:19:36,342 --> 00:19:36,882
‐ [Akito] Idiot!

530
00:19:37,009 --> 00:19:38,719
(Yurika crying)

531
00:19:38,844 --> 00:19:40,974
‐ Incidentally, I’ve
been relaying the feed

532
00:19:41,055 --> 00:19:43,565
from the Aestivalis to
every ship in the area.

533
00:19:43,683 --> 00:19:45,183
‐ So this is the
lovers spat that

534
00:19:45,267 --> 00:19:46,807
will decide the fate
of the universe.

535
00:19:46,894 --> 00:19:48,354
‐ Uh huh.

536
00:19:48,479 --> 00:19:51,269
‐ [Yurika] I’m not stupid,
quit calling me that!

537
00:19:51,357 --> 00:19:54,027
‐ Yurika, I watched
the last episode

538
00:19:54,151 --> 00:19:56,111
of Gekigangar Three last night.

539
00:19:56,195 --> 00:19:57,525
‐ Huh?

540
00:19:57,613 --> 00:20:00,323
‐ Yeah, and it was the
worst episode of the series.

541
00:20:00,408 --> 00:20:01,698
(gentle music)

542
00:20:01,784 --> 00:20:03,374
But as awful as it was,

543
00:20:03,494 --> 00:20:06,874
I felt shivers going down
my spine as I watched it.

544
00:20:06,997 --> 00:20:09,327
Seeing Gekigangar Three
and Gekigangar Five

545
00:20:09,417 --> 00:20:11,587
fighting side by
side with each other.

546
00:20:11,711 --> 00:20:13,461
‐ [Yurika] Side by side.

547
00:20:13,546 --> 00:20:14,956
Sounds kind of nice.

548
00:20:15,047 --> 00:20:16,257
‐ [Akito] I guess there’s
a part of me that wants

549
00:20:16,382 --> 00:20:18,722
to believe in perfect
good, happy endings,

550
00:20:18,843 --> 00:20:20,343
and hot blooded passion.

551
00:20:20,428 --> 00:20:23,218
The part of me that
loves Gekigangar‐‐

552
00:20:23,305 --> 00:20:25,675
‐ Is the part of you that’s
in love with me, isn’t it?

553
00:20:25,766 --> 00:20:27,226
‐ Look, I was just
about to make a major

554
00:20:27,309 --> 00:20:28,939
and very profound
speech here, damn it!

555
00:20:29,061 --> 00:20:31,401
But since you mentioned
it, yes I do, you wacko.

556
00:20:31,522 --> 00:20:34,192
You’re supposed to say
something back, you know.

557
00:20:34,275 --> 00:20:34,865
‐ Excuse me?

558
00:20:34,942 --> 00:20:36,192
You know how I feel.

559
00:20:36,277 --> 00:20:39,487
I love you with all my
heart and soul Akito!

560
00:20:39,572 --> 00:20:41,492
‐ That’s the first time
I’ve heard you say it.

561
00:20:41,574 --> 00:20:42,534
‐ It is not!

562
00:20:42,616 --> 00:20:43,576
‐ I’m sure it is.

563
00:20:43,659 --> 00:20:44,579
‐ It is not.

564
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:45,580
‐ Yes it is.

565
00:20:45,703 --> 00:20:46,583
‐ It is not!

566
00:20:46,704 --> 00:20:47,504
‐ Is too!

567
00:20:47,580 --> 00:20:48,330
‐ No, it’s not!

568
00:20:48,414 --> 00:20:49,214
‐ Yes it is!

569
00:20:49,290 --> 00:20:51,920
(romantic music)

570
00:20:53,586 --> 00:20:54,956
‐ [Yurika] I love you Akito.

571
00:20:57,256 --> 00:20:59,216
‐ [Ruri] So all of that
being said and done,

572
00:20:59,300 --> 00:21:02,090
I still have to wonder if
kissing was really essential

573
00:21:02,178 --> 00:21:04,138
for the two of them to
start the Boson Jump.

574
00:21:04,263 --> 00:21:05,933
All Ms. Fressange would
say is that when I was

575
00:21:06,056 --> 00:21:08,516
a little older I
would know the truth.

576
00:21:08,601 --> 00:21:12,901
In the end, a lot of big
mysteries remained unexplained,

577
00:21:12,980 --> 00:21:14,610
like the meaning of
the plate that Ai gave

578
00:21:14,690 --> 00:21:17,900
to her older self, and who
the ancient martians were,

579
00:21:17,985 --> 00:21:19,985
and what happened to
their civilization.

580
00:21:20,112 --> 00:21:22,912
Still, since we had the
calculation unit from

581
00:21:22,990 --> 00:21:25,580
the ruin onboard the
Nadesico, we were able

582
00:21:25,659 --> 00:21:27,079
to Boson Jump far away.

583
00:21:27,161 --> 00:21:30,461
The war between Jupiter and
the Earth will probably go on,

584
00:21:30,539 --> 00:21:32,959
but they won’t be able to
do much more than growl

585
00:21:33,042 --> 00:21:34,542
at each other for a while.

586
00:21:34,627 --> 00:21:37,087
I guess we’ll have to wait
for another opportunity

587
00:21:37,171 --> 00:21:40,011
to find out what happens next,
in the inevitable sequel.

588
00:21:41,759 --> 00:21:44,259
(gentle music)

